SIMPLE: idiopathy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idiopathy
<hw>Id`i*op"a*thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Idiopathies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>'i`dios</grk> proper, peculiar + <?/, <?/, to suffer: cf. F.
<ets>idiopathie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A peculiar, or
individual, characteristic or affection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All men are so full of their own fancies and
<qex>idiopathies</qex>, that they scarce have the civility to
interchange any words with a stranger.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid state or condition not
preceded or occasioned by any other disease; a primary
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idiophanous</ent>⟦br⟧
